          p Tokens will be distributed proportionally among the participants according to the amount of received stakes.
      .row.content
        .col-md-12
          h4 Bounty
          ul.bulleted
            li Unilot.io ICO ANN thread opening post translation: 50 stakes
            li Activity in the local ANN thread: 1 stakes per 1 post (yours) in your ANN thread
            li Translation of the Unilot.io Whitepaper to your language: 50 stakes
            li Bonus for posting on a different forums besides the Bitcointalk: 1 Stake (before the posting you have to get our approval)

          h4 Rules
          ul.bulleted
            li Using Google Translate and other online translators is not allowed. Participants using Google Translate will be instantly disqualified.
            li One person can reserve only one language for translation.
          p We offer bounty program participants translate information in the following languages:
          ul.bulleted
            li Chinese  
            li Arabic
            li French
            li German
            li Italian
            li Indonesian
            li Turkish
            li Hindi
            li Hungarian
            li Portuguese
            li Greek
            li Dutch
            li Spanish
            li Japanese
            li Korean
          p Haven't found your language in the list but still want to handle translation and community management? Contact us by e-mail - #[a(href="mailto:bounty@unilot.io" target="_blank") bounty@unilot.io]

          h4 How to join
          ol.numbered
            li Sign up on our official website of the bounty program: #[a(href="https://unilot.io/en-us/cp/sign-up.html" target="_blank") https://unilot.io/en-us/cp/sign-up.html] and make a request for the participation in the Translation & Community management campaign, reserve the language.
            li We'll review your request and contact you to discuss the details or confirm your participation.
          
          h4 Questions?
          p If you have any questions regarding the translation/community management campaign, please, use the Unilot.io Slack for the communication. It will be the fastest way to communicate.
          p Just sign in to Unilot.io Steemit and send a message to #[span.todo #Unilot.io_] channel to discuss the details.
